extraction of a time series for a given point¶

In this first example, we want to extract a time series of the shaded fraction of the sun area for a given point of coordinate (45°N, 0°E).

In [4]:
ilat,ilon=307,197

lat=data_nc["latitude"][ilon,ilat]
lon=data_nc["longitude"][ilon,ilat]

time=[dt.datetime(2000,1,1,0,0)+dt.timedelta(seconds=int(x)) for x in data_nc["time"][:].data]
rel_sun_si2=data_nc["rel_sun_si2"][:,ilon,ilat].data
Gcs_max_control=data_nc["Gcs_max_control"][:,ilon,ilat].data
Gcs_max_eclipse=data_nc["Gcs_max_eclipse"][:,ilon,ilat].data

extraction of map for a given time step¶

In this second example, we want to extract a map of the shaded fraction of the sun area for for a given time step (10/06/2021 10:46).

iTime=120
lat=data_nc["latitude"][:,:]
lon=data_nc["longitude"][:,:]
time=nc.num2date(data_nc["time"][iTime],units=data_nc["time"].units)
rel_sun_vis=data_nc["rel_sun_vis"][iTime,:,:].data
Gcs_max_control=data_nc["Gcs_max_control"][iTime,:,:].data
Gcs_max_eclipse=data_nc["Gcs_max_eclipse"][iTime,:,:].data

Maximal absolute reduction of the clear sky irradiance due to the eclipse in each of the EU countries¶

In [15]:
time=[dt.datetime(2000,1,1,0,0)+dt.timedelta(seconds=int(x)) for x in data_nc["time"][:].data]

CountryID=['FR','HR','HU','AL','AT','BE','BG','CH','CY','CZ','DE','DK','EE','EL','IE','ES','FI',\
         'IS','PT','RO','RS','SE','SI','SK','TR','UK','NO','IT','LI','LT','LU','LV','ME','MK',\
         'MT','NL','PL']
CountryID=data_nc["CountryID"][:,:]

Time_MaxCSRed=[]
Val_MaxCSRed=[]

for iTime,Time in enumerate(time):
    print(iTime)
    Gcs_max_control=data_nc["Gcs_max_control"][iTime,:,:].data
    Gcs_max_eclipse=data_nc["Gcs_max_eclipse"][iTime,:,:].data
    dGcs=Gcs_max_control-Gcs_max_eclipse    
    
    for iCnty,CTY in enumerate(CountryID):
        tAvgGcsRed=np.mean(dGcs[CountryID==iCnty+1])
        
        if iTime==0:
            Time_MaxCSRed.append(Time)
            Val_MaxCSRed.append(tAvgGcsRed)
        else:
            if (Val_MaxCSRed[iCnty]<tAvgGcsRed):
                Time_MaxCSRed[iCnty]=Time
                Val_MaxCSRed[iCnty]=tAvgGcsRed

Preparation of the raster to display the maximal impact of the eclipse per country¶

In [53]:
lat=data_nc["latitude"][:,:]
lon=data_nc["longitude"][:,:]

MapCNTYRed=np.zeros(lon.shape)
for iCnty,CTY in enumerate(CountryID):
    
    if iCnty==0:
        CountryLat=np.mean(lat[MapCNTYID==iCnty+1])
        CountryLon=np.mean(lon[MapCNTYID==iCnty+1])
    else:
        CountryLat=np.append(CountryLat,np.mean(lat[MapCNTYID==iCnty+1]))
        CountryLon=np.append(CountryLon,np.mean(lon[MapCNTYID==iCnty+1]))
    
    if not np.isin(CTY,['NO','IS','SE','FI','TR']):
        MapCNTYRed[MapCNTYID==iCnty+1]=Val_MaxCSRed[iCnty]

plot of the results¶

In [60]:
plt.figure(figsize=(20,15))
ixSC=(MapCNTYID>0) & (MapCNTYRed>0)
orig_map=plt.cm.get_cmap('viridis')
reversed_map = orig_map.reversed()

CLR=plt.scatter(lon[ixSC],lat[ixSC],c=MapCNTYRed[ixSC],cmap=reversed_map)
for iCnty,CTY in enumerate(CountryID):
    Str=CTY+"\n"+Time_MaxCSRed[iCnty].strftime("%H:%M")
    if (CountryLat[iCnty]<60) & (CountryLon[iCnty]<30):
        if Val_MaxCSRed[iCnty]<80:
            plt.text(CountryLon[iCnty],CountryLat[iCnty],Str,ha='center',fontsize=16)
        else:
            plt.text(CountryLon[iCnty],CountryLat[iCnty],Str,color='w',ha='center',fontsize=16)
cbar = plt.colorbar(CLR)
cbar.set_label('Maximal reduction of the clear sky irradiance due to the eclipse [W/m2]',fontsize=18)
plt.xlabel('longitude [°]',fontsize=18)
plt.ylabel('latitude [°]',fontsize=18)
plt.title('Magnitude and time of the maximal impact \n of the eclipse on the clear sky irradiance',\
          fontsize=26)

Time series of the country averaged effect of the eclipse for a selected number of countries¶

In [9]:
time=[dt.datetime(2000,1,1,0,0)+dt.timedelta(seconds=int(x)) for x in data_nc["time"][:].data]

CountryID=['FR','HR','HU','AL','AT','BE','BG','CH','CY','CZ','DE','DK','EE','EL','IE','ES','FI',\
         'IS','PT','RO','RS','SE','SI','SK','TR','UK','NO','IT','LI','LT','LU','LV','ME','MK',\
         'MT','NL','PL']
MapCNTYID=data_nc["CountryID"][:,:]

SelectedCNTY=['IE', 'UK', 'DK', 'EE' , 'FR', 'BE', 'DE', 'PL' , 'PT', 'ES', 'IT', 'RO']
AvgGcsControl=np.zeros((len(time),len(SelectedCNTY)))
AvgGcsEclipse=np.zeros((len(time),len(SelectedCNTY)))
for iTime,Time in enumerate(time):
    print(iTime)
    tGcsRef=data_nc["Gcs_max_control"][iTime,:,:].data
    tGcsEcl=data_nc["Gcs_max_eclipse"][iTime,:,:].data

    for iCNTY0,CNTY in enumerate(SelectedCNTY):
    
        for j,X in enumerate(CountryID):
            if CNTY==X:
                iCNTY=j
    
        for iCnty,CTY in enumerate(CountryID):
            AvgGcsControl[iTime,iCNTY0]=np.mean(tGcsRef[MapCNTYID==iCNTY+1])
            AvgGcsEclipse[iTime,iCNTY0]=np.mean(tGcsEcl[MapCNTYID==iCNTY+1])

plot of the results¶

In [10]:
from matplotlib.dates import DateFormatter

plt.figure(figsize=(20,18))

for iCNTY,CNTY in enumerate(SelectedCNTY):
    ax=plt.subplot(4,4,iCNTY+1)
    plt.plot(time,AvgGcsControl[:,iCNTY],time,AvgGcsEclipse[:,iCNTY])
    plt.legend(('control','eclipse'))
    plt.title(CNTY,fontsize=20)
    if iCNTY>=8:
        plt.xlabel('Time',fontsize=18)
    if np.isin(iCNTY,[0,4,8]):
        plt.ylabel('Clear sky irradiance\n [W/m2]',fontsize=18)
    ax.xaxis.set_major_formatter( DateFormatter("%H"))

export of the results as csv data¶

In [98]:
iCNTY=4

import csv


with open('eclipse'+SelectedCNTY[iCNTY]+'.csv', 'w', newline='') as csvfile:
    fieldnames = ['time', 'AvgGcsControl','AvgGcsEclipse']
    writer = csv.DictWriter(csvfile, fieldnames=fieldnames)
    writer.writeheader()
    for ii,tTime in enumerate(time):
        writer.writerow({'time': time[ii].strftime("%d-%m-%Y %H:%M"),\
                         'AvgGcsControl': AvgGcsControl[ii,iCNTY],\
                         'AvgGcsEclipse': AvgGcsEclipse[ii,iCNTY]})
